description: The Ultimate Artichoke offers the perfect combination of irresistible flavor, simple preparation and endless possibilities. Our tender artichokes are hand-peeled, confitted in EVOO and hand-packed. They have been developed to easily and quickly "open" to resemble a large blooming flower. Once grilled or fried, the artichokes' high natural sugar content develops a subtle caramelized flavor to create a flavorful, beautifully plated and healthy dish. Made with only two ingredients, artichokes and EVOO, this culinary standout contains 30% more natural sugar than other artichokes due to the variety (Tudela) and growing conditions. Further, these artichokes are hand-peeled and do not contain hard-to-eat, fibrous outer leaves. You'll enjoy the taste of pure artichoke, without flavor enhancements such as vinegar, herbs and spices. Traditionally grown and harvested in Spain's southeastern Mediterranean region, our artichokes are packaged with 8 hours of harvest for the utmost freshness.
name: The Ultimate Artichoke

description: The black cherry, of the Prunus Avium family, is the sweet cousin of the sour cherry, Prunus Cerasus. Cherries are the first pit fruits of the summer. It’s estimated that there are over 600 varieties of sweet cherries, including black cherries, of which the best-known in the English-speaking world are Bings, Chelons, Sweethearts and Tulanes. They are rich in natural sugars and tannins and are appreciated as table fruits and base ingredients for jams and pastries. The Romans or Greeks first brought cherries to Europe from the Caspian Sea, mainly using sour varieties to accompany meat-based dishes until the Middle-Ages, but little by little, the sweet black cherry, became a dessert fruit and a base for sweet condiments. Cherries also traveled east to China and Japan and, of course, their blooming flowers have become central to celebrating spring in Japan, as well as Washington, DC. In France, Louis XV loved the fruit and boosted its cultivation, also encouraging artisans to use its hard and regular wood for his elaborate style of furniture. The cherry became the royal fruit par excellence, replacing the strawberry of which Louis XIV, his great grandfather, had been the great defender. The cherry moved across the ocean to North America in the 16th Century and black cherries are today mainly grown in the western parts of the US and Canada. High in vitamin A, B et C content, rich in trace minerals such as a potassium, magnesium and calcium, they are among the healthiest of fruits. Their sweet, juicy flavor, their deep color and distinctive aroma make cherries the very epitome of the start of summer.
name: IQF Cherry Griottes

description: The Ultimate Artichoke offers the perfect combination of irresistible flavor, simple preparation and endless possibilities. Our tender artichokes are hand-peeled, confitted in EVOO and hand-packed. They have been developed to easily and quickly "open" to resemble a large blooming flower. Once grilled or fried, the artichokes' high natural sugar content develops a subtle caramelized flavor to create a flavorful, beautifully plated and healthy dish. Made with only two ingredients, artichokes and EVOO, this culinary standout contains 30% more natural sugar than other artichokes due to the variety (Tudela) and growing conditions. Further, these artichokes are hand-peeled and do not contain hard-to-eat, fibrous outer leaves. You'll enjoy the taste of pure artichoke, without flavor enhancements such as vinegar, herbs and spices. Traditionally grown and harvested in Spain's southeastern Mediterranean region, our artichokes are packaged with 8 hours of harvest for the utmost freshness.

description: An exquisite dessert, Bridor Frozen French Cinnamon Swirls are created in France with a deliciously buttery recipe. These tasty pastries are pre-proofed, pre-egg washed, frozen and ready to bake for your convenience. Our Cinnamon swirls offer a harmonious blend of buttery pastry and sweet, aromatic cinnamon. The aroma is warm and inviting, with notes of freshly baked goodness that enliven your senses. What sets our Cinnamon Swirls apart is their versatility and delightful sweetness. Whether you're serving them as a scrumptious breakfast indulgence, pairing them with a scoop of ice cream for dessert, or incorporating them into creative recipes, these twists will bring a burst of indulgent sweetness and a comforting hint of cinnamon warmth to your menu.

description: This Vanilla Bean Gelato is proof that magic can happen when you go back to the basics. description: Shoestring French fries are a type of French fry that is made from fresh potatoes that have been cut into thin, long strips and then fried until crispy and golden brown. They are similar in shape to thin shoelaces, hence the name "shoestring". Shoestring French fries are typically made from high-quality potatoes that are cut into thin, uniform strips to ensure even cooking. They are often seasoned with salt or other spices and can be served with a variety of dipping sauces, such as ketchup, mayonnaise, or aioli. Shoestring French fries are a popular side dish or snack, and are often found in fast food restaurants, diners, and pubs. They are a great complement to sandwiches, burgers, and other main dishes, and are also a popular bar snack.
name: Shoestring Classic French Fries

description: Say goodbye to the laborious task of peeling, boiling, and mashing potatoes. Available exclusively through The Chefs' Warehouse, our Mashed Potato Pellets are a game-changer, ready to use straight from the bag. Prepare creamy, velvety mashed potatoes in minutes, freeing up your valuable time for culinary creativity. Belgian potato varietals are peeled, cooked, extruded into pellets and then individually quick frozen. Conveniently portioned, these labor saving pellets  transform easily into consistent mashed potatoes every time! description: Shoestring French fries are a type of French fry that is made from fresh potatoes that have been cut into thin, long strips and then fried until crispy and golden brown. They are similar in shape to thin shoelaces, hence the name "shoestring". Shoestring French fries are typically made from high-quality potatoes that are cut into thin, uniform strips to ensure even cooking. They are often seasoned with salt or other spices and can be served with a variety of dipping sauces, such as ketchup, mayonnaise, or aioli. Shoestring French fries are a popular side dish or snack, and are often found in fast food restaurants, diners, and pubs. They are a great complement to sandwiches, burgers, and other main dishes, and are also a popular bar snack.

description: Shoestring French fries are a type of French fry that is made from fresh potatoes that have been cut into thin, long strips and then fried until crispy and golden brown. They are similar in shape to thin shoelaces, hence the name "shoestring". Shoestring French fries are typically made from high-quality potatoes that are cut into thin, uniform strips to ensure even cooking. They are often seasoned with salt or other spices and can be served with a variety of dipping sauces, such as ketchup, mayonnaise, or aioli. Shoestring French fries are a popular side dish or snack, and are often found in fast food restaurants, diners, and pubs. description: Straight cut French fries are a classic type of French fry that is made from fresh potatoes that have been cut into long, thin strips and then fried until crispy and golden brown. They are a popular side dish or snack and can be served on their own or as a complement to burgers, sandwiches, and other main dishes. Straight cut French fries are typically made from high-quality potatoes that are cut to a consistent size and thickness to ensure even cooking.
